    "headerDoc": "STEP 948 — Graph Theory and Combinatorics Conjectures\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-21\n\n  Five graph-theoretic open problems:\n\n  A. HADWIGER'S CONJECTURE (chromatic number vs minor)\n     χ(G) ≤ k implies G has K_k as minor? OPEN for k ≥ 7.\n     Proved: k ≤ 6 (Robertson et al. 1993). Verified small cases.\n\n  B. RECONSTRUCTION CONJECTURE (Kelly-Ulam 1960)\n     Every graph on ≥ 3 vertices is determined by its deck.\n     OPEN for general graphs. Verified for small graphs.\n\n  C. GRACEFUL TREE CONJECTURE (Kotzig-Ringel 1963)\n     Every tree has a graceful labeling (edges get distinct values 1..n-1).\n     OPEN. Ver"
